line_1: TELL me what Genius did the art invent,
line_2: The lively image of the voice to paint;

line_1: The lively image of the voice to paint;
line_2: TELL me what Genius did the art invent,

line_1: Who first the secret how to colour sound,
line_2: And to give shape to reason, wisely found;

line_1: And to give shape to reason, wisely found;
line_2: Who first the secret how to colour sound,

line_1: With bodies how to cloath ideas, taught;
line_2: And how to draw the picture of a thought:

line_1: And how to draw the picture of a thought:
line_2: With bodies how to cloath ideas, taught;

line_1: Who taught the hand to speak, the eye to hear
line_2: A silent language roving far and near;

line_1: A silent language roving far and near;
line_2: Who taught the hand to speak, the eye to hear

line_1: Whose softest noise outstrips loud thunder's sound,
line_2: And spreads her accents thro' the world's vast round:

line_1: And spreads her accents thro' the world's vast round:
line_2: Whose softest noise outstrips loud thunder's sound,

line_1: A voice heard by the deaf, spoke by the dumb,
line_2: Whose echo reaches long, long time to come;

line_1: Whose echo reaches long, long time to come;
line_2: A voice heard by the deaf, spoke by the dumb,

line_1: Which dead men speak as well as those alive —
line_2: Tell me what Genius did this art contrive.

line_1: Tell me what Genius did this art contrive.
line_2: Which dead men speak as well as those alive —
